# CBraMod — NeurIPS 2025 EEG Challenge

> 🚧 **Work in progress**

---

## 🏆 Competition Results — [NeurIPS 2025 EEG Challenge](https://eeg2025.github.io)

This repository contains our submission to the 2025 NeurIPS EEG Challenge, a competition with **1,183 teams** and over **8,000 submissions** on CodaBench.

| Phase | Rank |
|-------|------|
| Challenge 1 (warm-up) | 🥉 **3rd** |
| Challenge 2 (final) | **9th** |

> Final standings were GPU-limited — further training of V5/V6 and ensemble strategies were left unexplored.

---

## 🧠 Model Versions

| Version | Key Changes |
|---------|-------------|
| **V1** | Baseline CBraMod. Depthwise Conv2d positional encoding, Hann window + LayerNorm preprocessing, simple magnitude+phase spectral projection. Shallow encoder (12 layers). |
| **V2** | Deepened encoder to 24 layers. Upgraded weight init to `trunc_normal` for linear layers. |
| **V3** | Replaced Conv2d PE with **channel self-attention**, enabling learned inter-channel relationships. Explicit 51-bin rFFT spectral projection. |
| **V4** | Introduced `EnhancedSpectralProjection` with learnable EEG band weights (δ/θ/α/β/γ), PSD features, and separate mag/phase/power projections. Added `spectral_gate` and learned `mask_token`. Preprocessing switched to **MAD-based robust standardization**. |
| **V5** | `EnhancedSpectralProjection` without spectral gate. Increased encoder attention heads to 10. Adapted for 200 Hz data. |
| **V6** | Added learnable `temporal_pos_encoding` for explicit patch-position encoding. Patch-level `LayerNorm` preprocessing. Retains gated spectral fusion and channel self-attention from V4. |

